1 . initialise npm init -y 2. create models and route folder 3. create index.js file 4. npm install express , dotenv , mongoose , bcryptjs , body-parser
(The body parser is used to pass the body of your request or turn json to object ), nodemailer 5. add type in the new init package.json to module 6. import express and dotenv 7. hide you port number in env and create server 8. create config folder and create db.js file, import mongoose from mongoose 9. await mongoose to wait for mongoose to connect before moving 10. Add the try and catch to catch if there is any error 10. import and export the mongo db function
